%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZaidi%20and%20his%20accomplices%20used%20to%20traffic%20vulnerable%20young%20Indian%20men%20to%20the%20Golden%20Triangle%20Region%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20where%20the%20borders%20of%20Thailand%2C%20Laos%20and%20Myanmar%20meet%2C%20and%20force%20them%20to%20work%20in%20Chinese%20companies.%20Their%20passports%20would%20be%20taken%20away%20as%20soon%20as%20these%20men%20reached%20abroad%20and%20they%20would%20be%20forced%20into%20cyber%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20Zaidi%20was%20constantly%20changing%20his%20location%20and%20the%20police%20had%20deployed%20teams%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20to%20catch%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20manual%20inputs%20and%20technical%20surveillance%2C%20Zaidi's%20location%20was%20finally%20traced%20to%20Hyderabad.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20arrested%20after%20a%20long%20persevering%20chase%20of%202%2C500%20kilometres%20by%20the%20team%20without%20any%20rest%20near%20Nampally%20Railway%20Station%20in%20Hyderabad%20while%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20escape%20another%20hideout%2C%26quot%3B%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20of%20Police%20(Special%20Cell)%20Manoj%20C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scam%20came%20to%20light%20after%20a%20First%20Information%20Report%20(FIR)%20was%20registered%20in%20New%20Friends%20Colony%20in%20Delhi%20on%20the%20complaint%20of%20a%20person%20named%20Naresh%20Lakhwat%20on%20May%2027.%20He%20had%20told%20the%20police%20that%20he%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20job%20when%20he%20came%20across%20a%20consultancy%20firm%20called%20Ali%20Internation%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20got%20job%20offers%20from%20Thailand%20and%20Laos%20through%20the%20firm.%20The%20company%20eventually%20sent%20him%20to%20Thailand%20where%20his%20passport%20was%20snatched%20and%20he%20was%20forced%20to%20work%20in%20a%20Chinese%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20company%20used%20to%20scam%20Indians%20online%2C%20Mr%20Lakhwat%20told%