20January%2019%20to%20sell%20its%20social%20media%20app%20to%20a%20non-Chinese%20company%20or%20face%20a%20nationwide%20ban.%20TikTok%20appealed%2C%20but%20on%20Friday%2C%20a%20federal%20court%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-details-when-how-legal-cases-trump-options%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupheld%20the%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20siding%20with%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20argument%20that%20the%20service%20poses%20a%20national%20security%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20Trump%20unsuccessfully%20sought%20to%20ban%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States%20but%20has%20since%20had%20a%20change%20of%20heart.%20During%20the%202024%20campaign%2C%20Trump%20said%20young%20people%20would%20%26quot%3Bgo%20crazy%20without%20it.%26quot%3B%20Trump's%20own%20TikTok%20accounts%20generated%20millions%20of%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20side%20Trump%20ultimately%20lands%20on%20the%20issue%20could%20have%20a%20major%20impact%20on%20ByteDance%20and%20TikTok%2C%20which%20says%20it%20has%20over%20170%20million%20users%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Even%20if%20the%20law%20is%20upheld%20after%20future%20appeals%2C%20Trump%20could%20choose%20not%20to%20enforce%20it%20during%20his%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20closest%20advisors%2C%20however%2C%20might%20have%20something%20to%20say%20about%20that.%20Some%20of%20Trump's%20top%20cabinet%20nominees%20support%20a%20TikTok%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Marco%20Rubio%20of%20Florida%20%E2%80%94%20Trump's%20nominee%20for%20secretary%20of%20state%20%E2%80%94%20called%20a%20ban%20a%20%26quot%3Bwin%20for%20America%26quot%3B%20earlier%20this%20year.%20Trump's%20pick%20for%20Federal%20Communications%20Commission%20chair%2C%20Brendan%20Carr%2C%20also%20advocated%20for%20a%20TikTok%20ban%20in%20Project%202025%2C%20a%20road%20map%20for%20the%20first%20180%20days%20of%20a%20new%20Republican%20presidency%20that%20the%20Heritage%20Foundation%2C%20a%20conservative%20think%20tank%2C%20p